    q: "Door is locked and oven won't open. What now?",
    a: "Three steps before calling. (1) Let the oven cool completely, 1 to 2 hours minimum after the cycle was supposed to end. Many self-clean locks are temperature-sensitive and won't release until the cavity is below 200°F. (2) Cut power at the breaker for 30 minutes, then restore. This resets some electronic latches. (3) If still stuck, mechanical motor replacement is needed, $440 to $640 typical."
  },
